quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  4,116,Allah does not forgive anything being associated with Him but He forgives whoever He wills for anything other than that. Anyone who associates something with Allah has gone very far astray
  4,117,What they call on apart from Him are female idols. What they call on is an arrogant shaytan
  4,118,"whom Allah has cursed. He said, ´I will take a certain fixed proportion of Your slaves"
  4,119,I will lead them astray and fill them with false hopes. I will command them and they will cut off cattle´s ears. I will command them and they will change Allah´s creation.´ Anyone who takes Shaytan as his protector in place of Allah has clearly lost everything
  4,120,He makes promises to them and fills them with false hopes. But what Shaytan promises them is nothing but delusion
  4,121,The shelter of such people will be Hell. They will find no way to escape from it
  4,122,"But as for those who have iman and do right actions, We will admit them into Gardens with rivers flowing under them, remaining in them timelessly, for ever and ever. Allah´s promise is true. Whose speech could be truer than Allah´s"
  4,123,It is not a matter of wishful thinking on your part nor of the wishful thinking of the People of the Book. Anyone who does evil will be repaid for it. He will not find any protector or helper besides Allah
  4,124,"Anyone, male or female, who does right actions and is a mumin, will enter the Garden. They will not be wronged by so much as the tiniest speck"
  4,125,"Who could have a better deen than someone who submits himself completely to Allah and is a good-doer, and follows the religion of Ibrahim, a man of pure natural belief? Allah took Ibrahim as an intimate friend"
  4,126,What is in the heavens and in the earth belongs to Allah. Allah encompasses all things